PRACTICE EXAM

A small company has nearly 200 users who already have AWS accounts in the company AWS environment. A new S3 bucket has been created which will allow roughly a third of all users access to sensitive information in the bucket. What is the most time efficient way to get these users access to the bucket?
A. Create a new bucket policy granting the appropriate permissions and attach it to the bucket.
B. Create a new policy which will grant permissions to the bucket. Create a role and attach the policy to that role. Add the users to this role.
C. Create a new role which will grant permissions to the bucket. Create a group and attach the role to that group. Add the users to this group.
D. Create a new policy which will grant permissions to the bucket. Create a group and attach the policy to that group. Add the users to this group.
Answer : 


